news.title: Kohinoor Group buys 32 acre land in Pune for Rs 200 crore
news.para: Property consultant Anarock said it facilitated the deal between the two parties. The deal for 32 acres of prime land at Wagholi has been concluded.

news.title: As protests continue, Haryana CM orders structural audit of Chintels Paradiso
news.para: ​As residents of several other housing societies in New Gurugram expressed apprehensions about the safety of their buildings, Khattar also asked the local administration to identify all such buildings through the town and country planning department or the residents' welfare associations and get their audits done at the builders' expense.

news.title: Migsun takes over Parsvnath Palacia in Greater Noida
news.para: Spread over 9 acres, the 2 and 3 BHK apartments in 1320 sq ft to 1835 sq ft configurations. The project, with six towers and 442 units, provides a vast range of amenities including Cycling & Jogging Track, Gymnasium, Swimming Pool and Lift.

news.title: Rajasthan: Green nod to 60 bajri mining leases, a relief for industry
news.para: With the clearance, the bajri prices are expected to fall sharply which had gone up to Rs 1 lakh a truck. After the Supreme Court’s conditional nod, about six mines have been made operational in the state.

news.title: Rail Land Development Authority to lease Bengaluru land Rs 90 crore
news.para: The land is ideally suited for residential and mixed-use development. Subject to the local bye laws, the bidder will have the discretion to plan, organize and construct the development project to suit their business plan. The permissible FAR for the site is 3.0.

news.title: Indore admin sends notices to three banks for mortgaging land of Satellite Hills colony
news.para: In a notice issued by the additional collector Abhay Bedekar to “The chief managers of Union Bank, M G road branch, Punjab National Bank, Manoramaganj branch and UCO Bank, Palasia branch, they are asked to submit replies on the matter by February 21,” said an official press release from the district administration.

news.title: Mysuru development body stops inviting applications from site seekers
news.para: Sometime back, the number of applicants seeking sites from the urban development body was around 80,000 and authorities had been promising to provide them sites.

news.title: Nashik civic body plans GIS mapping of entire city
news.para: The digital mapping of all the city roads, properties, green and yellow areas of the city along with underground drainage lines, piped gas lines and various ducts have been planned by the civic body.

news.title: Jaipur development body to sell seized plots to build colonies
news.para: After auctioning these plots, the civic body will complete the development work in these colonies. The move will benefit lakhs of people who were deprived of basic facilities including roads, sewerage, parks after purchasing plots from private developers.

news.title: Prestige Group to set up investment funds worth $500 million
news.para: The proposed funds will be targeted at institutional investors and high net worth individuals (HNIs). They will also look at acquiring stressed residential projects and those that have gone to the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT).

news.title: Ramky Estates to develop Grade-A office space for Genpact in Hyderabad
news.para: Ramky Estates will build 20 lakh sq ft of Grade A IT/ ITES office space and 9 lakh sq ft of residential space at the location over five years.

news.title: Gurugram: Give us a proper place to stay, say residents of Chintels Paradiso tower
news.para: The residents have been staying with their friends or relatives since February 10, when the floors caved in. On Sunday, the flat owners gheraoed an official of developer Chintels who visited Paradiso in the morning.

news.title: Take stringent action against Chintels Paradiso's builder, if not, will intensify protest: RWAs
news.para: The representatives of 50 housing societies have lent their support to the residents of Chintels Paradiso who have been rendered homeless after a vertical collapse of the living rooms of five flats from the sixth to the first floors in one of the towers.

news.title: Redevelopment benefit linked to area, not income: Bombay HC
news.para: At least 48 old buildings are being redeveloped in Samata Nagar. The six occupants said their building is in the middle-income group (MIG) category but they occupy 18sqm tenements.

news.title: Will tweak policy for granting OCs to buildings: Haryana deputy CM
news.para: Currently, the department of town and country planning (DTCP) issues an OC to a developer after checking if the building has been constructed in keeping with the approved layout plan and the Haryana Building Code. There is no provision to check the quality of construction at the time of granting the OC.
